summary: I’m currently reading Neil Gaiman’s Good Omens script book and I am thoroughly enjoying it, especially these directions and...
body:
I’m currently reading Neil Gaiman’s Good Omens script book and I am thoroughly enjoying it, especially these directions and little notes sprinkled about. Here are my favorites:

The nanny, wearing dark glasses, reminds us of Crowley. She’s sexy and domineering.

The plants are terrified. No, I don’t know how we show this on television either.

Crowley flares at him, glarefully.

HUGE EXPLOSION. FIRE AND LIGHT AND THINGS BEING BLOWN AROUND. SO COOL AN EXPLOSION THAT I AM TYPING IN CAPITALS.

Crowley’s bedroom. We see a montage of Crowley trying to get to sleep by lying on the bed, on the wall, then on the ceiling. CLOSE UP of his snake-eyes. He’s wide-awake. Then he puts on his dark glasses.

Can someone please draw Crowley attempting to fall asleep in all of those places and then calling Aziraphale to meet up at their third (romantic) rendezvous!!!

summary: Azzy and Crowley, or why I'm laughing this week.
body:
Azzy and Crowley, or why I’m laughing this week.

So, I read the book Good Omens in middle school, a yellowed old copy that my dad, sister and I share. Much like the late Terry Pratchet and @neil-gaiman wrote as a suggestion in the forward, we have loved this book for years, with crumbs and stains in the pages galore.

Saying this, the three of us have been disappointed to be unable to see the show until much later than the first day it came out. I’ve been trolling this site a bit and found that everyone loves it as well, and that the couple I knew as “ineffable husbands” is being touted as asexual icons. I have only one thing to say: WE BEEN KNEW.

I feel like this is great that everyone else loves this too, though, so the more the merrier!

summary: So my head is saying that despite Crowley helping to create a nebula and constantly talking about going to alpha centauri and...
body:
So my head is saying that despite Crowley helping to create a nebula and constantly talking about going to alpha centauri and just space in general, he cant actually go there without angelic powers, his demonic powers cannot get him close to what he once created as an angel.  He needs Aziraphale to take him there (it’s partly why he’s always asking him, and why he didn’t go after he thought Zira was dead).

I just want one day not long after the first day of the rest of their lives for Aziraphale to finally say yes, lets go there for a holiday or something, and now the panic about the end of the world is over even Aziraphale gets quite excited at the prospect of seeing how the universe is getting along now, and cannot understand why Crowley seems so…sad, now they were finally going. Isn’t this what he’d wanted for ages?

Crowley meekly explains that Aziraphale will need to carry him with him on his celestial magic to get there, and that he hasn’t been able to see his nebula or anything else he created up there since he fell.  Aziraphale goes all soft (trademark) and of course holds on to him to take them there. When they do, and the two of them are standing on a distant planet that Crowley instantly recognises as one of his own, he stares up at his nebula that is so so close here, remembering the angelic energy that once flew through him and focusing it up, up, up so high to create those colours and mists and glistening lights.  

The Blue Giant sun that he had created still shined its ethereal blue light down on them where they stood, and all Crowley can do is stare in wonder at the universe.  It was so small when he was here, when it first started, when he was assigned to be one of the angels to help God build her magnificent ideas, and now it went on for so long and so far, there was just so much. His work was now just a tiny blip.

But it was all still here, God hadn’t destroyed what he’d created, even after he’d fell she’d left it all here. His mark of the angel he once was.

“You’re still up there, Crowley.” Aziraphale says softly, watching him watch the universe, taking his hand when he realises it’s shaking.
